author: Allyson Reedy
title: It's your final chance to vote for the top breakfast burrito in Denver
text:
Denver’s breakfast burrito battle is down to these 8 elite eateries 
No. 1 seed Santiago’s, largely considered the favorite in the tournament, lost to No. 3 Little Anita’s in a buzzer-beater. Our tortilla-clad Cinderella is none other than the 16 th Street Mall cart, No. 5 Asada Rico, which took down No. 1 Bonfire Burritos in a real nail-biter. 
Anything can happen in the final round. Will Little Anita’s continue its march to breakfast burrito glory? Will the clock finally strike midnight for our Cinderella? Will we ever recover from eating so many damn breakfast burritos? Stop the madness! (No really; we’re so sick of breakfast burritos.) 
Voting will close on Sunday, April 2. ELIMINATED: (3) The breakfast burrito from Emilio's Almost Famous , a Westminster bar and restaurant, all dressed up in guac and green chile. Emilio’s Almost Famous – 10081 Wadsworth Pkwy., Westminster, 303-465-6089, EmiliosAlmostFamous.com, Mon.-Fri. 7 a.m. – 9 p.m., Sat.-Sun. 9 a.m. – 9 p.m. (Provided by Emilio's Almost Famous) (3) Little Anita's vs. (5) Asada Rico Little Anita's
